(WBIR – KNOXVILLE) Another week of NFL action wraps up Monday night. Here’s how former Tennessee Volunteers played in their games from this past weekend. 
Peyton Manning: The Denver Broncos quarterback has seven 4-0 starts in his career, which is the most for a quarterback in NFL history. The Broncos defeated the Minnesota Vikings 23-20 on Sunday. 
Manning joined Brett Favre as the only quarterbacks to with 100 home starts in the NFL. 
Manning was 17 of 27 passing with 213 yards and one touchdown. He threw two interceptions. 
Arian Foster: Foster wasn’t very effective in his season debut after tearing his groin in training camp. 
On the ground, Foster had eight carries for 10 yards. Foster had three receptions for 25 yards receiving. 
The Houston Texans lost to the Atlanta Falcons 48-21. 
Foster had a fumble, which led to a Falcons touchdown. 
Arian Foster #23 of the Houston Texans is kept from recovering a fumble by O'Brien Schofield #50 of the Atlanta Falcons in the first half at the Georgia Dome on October 4, 2015 in Atlanta. (Photo: Scott Cunningham, Getty Images) 
Jason Witten: Witten had four receptions for 57 yards in the Dallas Cowboys 26-20 overtime loss to the New Orleans Saints. 
Eric Berry: Berry had five tackles in the Kansas City Chiefs 36-21 loss to the Cincinnati Bengals. 
Malik Jackson: Jackson had two tackles and 0.5 sack in the Broncos win over the Vikings. Denver had seven sacks against Minnesota on Sunday.
